headline: British American Tobacco and Altria Might Not Be Worth the Risk, but These 3 High-Yield Stocks Are
summary: British American Tobacco (NYSE: BTI) has a dividend yield of 7.2%, while Altria's (NYSE: MO) yield is 6.9%.  Enterprise Products Partners (NYSE: EPD), Enbridge (NYSE: ENB), and Realty Income (NYSE: O) have yields of 6.2%, 5.8%, and 5.6%, respectively.
